International Brief -- Delhaize Freres  Cie.:
   Belgian Retailer's Earnings
   Increased by 14% Last Year
Sales at Food Lion, through which Delhaize derives about
70% of its sales, rose 15% to $6.4 billion in 1991, Delhaize
said. During the year 103 new stores were opened, bringing
the total to 881. Some 125 new stores are planned for this
year, and Delhaize said it will have 2,000 Food Lion stores
operating by the year 2000.
   Super Discount Markets sales increased 9.2% to $253.6
million and the company swung to a profit in the second half
of the year, Delhaize said.